Reinforcement Learning, Probabilistic Methods. 

Reinforcement learning is the main topic of the paper, as it discusses how reinforcement learning can be used to learn models of the world's dynamics and enable planning at different levels of abstraction. 

Probabilistic methods are also mentioned, as the paper discusses how multi-time models can be used to predict what will happen, rather than when a certain event will take place. This involves probabilistic reasoning about the likelihood of different outcomes.
